{{NCAATeamSeason |Mode=Basketball |Year=2010&ndash;11 |Prev year=2009&ndash;10 |Next year=2011&ndash;12 |Team=South Florida Bulls |Image= Usfbulls newlogo.png |Conference=Big East Conference |Division= |ShortConference=Big East |CoachRank= |APRank= |Record= 10â23 |ConfRecord= 3â15 |HeadCoach=[[Stan Heath]] |AsstCoach1= |AsstCoach2= |AsstCoach3= |StadiumArena= [[USF Sun Dome]] |Champion= |BowlTourney= |BowlTourneyResult= }} {{2010&ndash;11 Big East men's basketball standings}} __FORCETOC__ The '''2010&ndash;11 South Florida Bulls men's basketball team''' represented the [[University of South Florida]] [[South Florida Bulls|Bulls]] during the [[2010â11 NCAA Division I men's basketball season]]. This was the 40th season of basketball for USF. The team was coached by [[Stan Heath]] in his fourth year at the school. USF played its home games in the [[USF Sun Dome]] and is a member of the [[Big East Conference]].
==Off season== During the off-season, there were several important milestones for the USF basketball program. In March, ground was broken on the Muma Basketball Center; a {{convert|50000|sqft|m2|adj=on}}, basketball practice facility, adjacent to the USF Sun Dome. Construction is expected to be completed by the end of spring 2011.<ref>http://www.gousfbulls.com/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=7700&ATCLID=204900191</ref> In June, [[Dominique Jones]] became the highest player ever drafted to the [[National Basketball Association|NBA]] from USF. He was selected in the first round, as the 25th overall pick by the [[Memphis Grizzlies]], and then traded to the [[Dallas Mavericks]].<ref>http://www.gousfbulls.com/ViewArticle.dbml?&DB_OEM_ID=7700&ATCLID=204963867&SPID=2923&SPSID=36686</ref> In August, the team represented the United States in Brazil for the 2010 Pan American University Championships. They took home the silver medal, losing in the finals to Brazil, and finishing with a record of 4-1. <ref>http://www.gousfbulls.com/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=7700&ATCLID=204943624</ref><ref>http://www.gousfbulls.com/ViewArticle.dbml?&DB_OEM_ID=7700&ATCLID=204974928&SPID=2923&SPSID=36686</ref> At Big East Media day in October, the Bulls were selected to finish in 13th place in the Big East Preseason Coaches' Poll.<ref>http://www.bigeast.org/News/tabid/435/Article/214542/Pittsburgh-Chosen-As-BIG-EAST-Hoops-Favorite.aspx</ref>
